Society.Habitats:
These predators could be found in virtually any river or lake on the [[Malatran Plateau]]. 

Friendly caiman katanga who dwelt in the waters of the [[Sleepy Lake]], to the southwest of the [[Fire Mountain]], were believed to protect the peaceful Nubari [[Zantira]] tribes that made homes atop lake rafts. Some Zantirans believed that the lake's caiman katanga saved the water spirit protector [[Jung'r'na]], who instructed the shapeshifters to protect the Raft Dweller humans.{{Cite polyhedron/113/Raft Dwellers: The Zantiri Tribe|6-7}}

Vile bands of the caiman katanga were known to occasionally raid peaceful [[Koshiva]] tribes of the Living Jungle.{{Cite polyhedron/102/Tribes of the Nubari|10}} River [[tam'hi]] harbored a distrust of caiman katanga as they often enough consumed the tam'hi young.
